93
00:06:00,650 --> 00:06:03,290
Ah! Because I want to eat it.

94
00:06:04,940 --> 00:06:05,820
That's it?

95
00:06:06,380 --> 00:06:07,150
Yeah.

96
00:06:15,610 --> 00:06:17,520
This isn't your first time making it, is it?

97
00:06:17,980 --> 00:06:19,960
Yeah, for hamburger steak.

98
00:06:23,780 --> 00:06:25,060
What do you usually eat?

99
00:06:26,530 --> 00:06:28,510
Udon or spaghetti and stuff like that.

100
00:06:29,150 --> 00:06:30,240
Sometimes I make somen noodles too.

101
00:06:36,760 --> 00:06:38,360
That just needs to be boiled for a bit, right?

102
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:39,170
Yeah.

103
00:06:46,390 --> 00:06:47,500
Let me do it.

104
00:06:48,260 --> 00:06:50,200
Mashiro, you make the salad.

105
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:51,050
OK.

106
00:06:58,050 --> 00:07:00,170
So he's still going to stay over, right?

107
00:07:02,510 --> 00:07:03,260
But.

108
00:07:03,390 --> 00:07:07,060
Even if we end up staying over,
it doesn't necessarily mean something's going to happen.

109
00:07:09,370 --> 00:07:10,720
But what if…

110
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:13,050
That really happened...

111
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:17,290
Even though I'm a little scared.

112
00:07:18,170 --> 00:07:20,370
I think it would be really happy.

113
00:07:25,760 --> 00:07:27,630
Are you going to cry or laugh? Pick one.

114
00:07:28,050 --> 00:07:28,770
Huh?

115
00:07:30,020 --> 00:07:32,310
I get that chopping onions can make you cry.

116
00:07:33,280 --> 00:07:34,830
Why do you keep giggling?

117
00:07:36,620 --> 00:07:37,660
It's nothing.

118
00:07:44,370 --> 00:07:45,880
Oh~

119
00:07:46,510 --> 00:07:47,850
This is so much fun!

120
00:07:48,300 --> 00:07:49,680
You sprinkled too much.

121
00:07:49,980 --> 00:07:51,790
Don't sweat the details so much.

122
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:53,630
I'll definitely make something super delicious for you, just watch.

123
00:07:54,790 --> 00:07:56,380
You're just mixing it, aren't you.

124
00:07:56,740 --> 00:07:57,900
For hamburger steak,

125
00:07:57,990 --> 00:08:00,000
This kneading step is the real key.

126
00:08:00,380 --> 00:08:02,710
Knead, knead.

127
00:08:04,520 --> 00:08:06,360
Ah! It's spilling everywhere.

128
00:08:11,490 --> 00:08:12,210
Okay.
Okay.

129
00:08:14,410 --> 00:08:15,340
You can answer it.

130
00:08:16,100 --> 00:08:16,840
It's okay.

131
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:18,670
This must be my mom again.

132
00:08:22,030 --> 00:08:23,240
I see.

133
00:08:25,140 --> 00:08:26,840
Stop worrying about it so much.

134
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:29,380
It's not like it's anything important anyway.

135
00:08:32,950 --> 00:08:34,420
Mixing it like this should be good enough, right?

136
00:08:35,590 --> 00:08:36,220
Yeah.

137
00:08:38,040 --> 00:08:40,410
Then let's start shaping it.

138
00:08:42,830 --> 00:08:43,720
I just feel like...

139
00:08:44,400 --> 00:08:46,970
A wall has been built between us.

140
00:08:50,900 --> 00:08:52,400
This is so good!

141
00:08:56,650 --> 00:08:58,370
Oh no, I can't stop.

142
00:08:58,930 --> 00:09:00,800
Calm down, take your time and eat slowly.

143
00:09:02,250 --> 00:09:04,730
If I'd known, I would've bought more meat.

144
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:12,080
I haven't touched this yet.

145
00:09:12,790 --> 00:09:13,560
Is that okay?

146
00:09:19,870 --> 00:09:20,530
Never mind.

147
00:09:21,180 --> 00:09:21,950
Huh?

148
00:09:23,210 --> 00:09:25,480
It's not every day we get to make hamburger steak together.

149
00:09:25,810 --> 00:09:27,490
I hope Kanade can also enjoy.

150
00:09:31,380 --> 00:09:32,580
Well then...

151
00:09:37,380 --> 00:09:38,340
Half for each of us.

152
00:09:39,580 --> 00:09:40,440
Thank you.

153
00:09:47,830 --> 00:09:49,520
This one tastes the best!

154
00:09:50,240 --> 00:09:51,950
They're all the same.

155
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:55,300
Is there any rice left?

156
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:56,350
