271
00:17:45,800 --> 00:17:47,480
That's because…

272
00:17:48,110 --> 00:17:51,950
He really cherishes you, Kanade, doesn't he?

273
00:17:53,340 --> 00:17:55,650
I also think the other person has probably become more cautious.

274
00:17:56,090 --> 00:17:58,150
Is that so?

275
00:17:59,070 --> 00:18:00,950
So, Kanade-san, in your heart,

276
00:18:01,240 --> 00:18:02,120
What do you think about it?
Yeah.

277
00:18:03,300 --> 00:18:03,930
Huh?

278
00:18:04,110 --> 00:18:05,490
If something like that happened,

279
00:18:05,560 --> 00:18:06,980
You don't mind it?

280
00:18:07,030 --> 00:18:07,860
What do you think?

281
00:18:09,300 --> 00:18:10,280
That's...

282
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:13,120
If you don't mind,

283
00:18:13,190 --> 00:18:13,950
Maybe next time…

284
00:18:14,030 --> 00:18:16,950
How about you take the initiative, Kanade-san?

285
00:18:17,010 --> 00:18:17,500
Oh!
I take the initiative?

286
00:18:18,290 --> 00:18:19,030
That's right.

287
00:18:22,770 --> 00:18:23,860
Otherwise…

288
00:18:24,030 --> 00:18:25,180
It'll just keep going like this forever.

289
00:18:25,270 --> 00:18:26,940
It might never change, you know.

290
00:18:27,220 --> 00:18:29,070
Maybe things will just stay the same
and nothing will ever change.

291
00:18:29,150 --> 00:18:30,000
Well then...

292
00:18:30,140 --> 00:18:31,500
What should I do?

293
00:18:32,350 --> 00:18:34,380
If backing down isn't an option...

294
00:18:35,340 --> 00:18:37,360
Just try making the first move!

295
00:18:47,050 --> 00:18:51,170
What should I do if I'm supposed to make the first move?

296
00:18:52,130 --> 00:18:53,120
I don't know.

297
00:18:53,160 --> 00:18:53,900
I don't know.

298
00:18:53,970 --> 00:18:55,370
I really have no idea!

299
00:19:07,200 --> 00:19:08,010
Wait...

300
00:19:11,590 --> 00:19:14,230
Why did I stop him back then?

301
00:19:23,040 --> 00:19:25,210
Because I was a little scared.

302
00:19:25,590 --> 00:19:28,010
It didn't feel like the Mashiro I usually know.

303
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:29,200
Why?

304
00:19:37,910 --> 00:19:41,410
Does Mashiro have a side I haven't seen yet?

305
00:19:47,520 --> 00:19:48,710
Mashiro is really scary.

306
00:19:52,780 --> 00:19:54,170
Then let's go.

307
00:19:55,430 --> 00:19:56,190
Huh?

308
00:19:57,090 --> 00:19:58,220
Let's go.

309
00:20:30,570 --> 00:20:32,840
Why do I feel so restless?

310
00:20:34,600 --> 00:20:39,300
(Mitsuko is calling)

311
00:20:39,880 --> 00:20:42,090
That curry place really is the best after all.

312
00:20:42,970 --> 00:20:44,640
Don't get an upset stomach again, okay?

313
00:20:44,680 --> 00:20:45,710
No problem.

314
00:20:45,760 --> 00:20:47,090
I only had level 5 spicy today.

315
00:20:49,120 --> 00:20:51,670
The movie you were looking for last time
is now available on the streaming platform.

316
00:20:51,670 --> 00:20:52,560
For real?

317
00:20:52,810 --> 00:20:54,350
How about we watch it together when we get home?

318
00:20:54,570 --> 00:20:55,360
Yeah.

319
00:20:55,840 --> 00:20:58,170
- I'm really looking forward to it.
- Yeah, me too.

320
00:20:58,800 --> 00:21:00,870
I wonder if that one's connected to the sequel.

321
00:21:00,870 --> 00:21:01,880
Kosuke!

322
00:21:09,760 --> 00:21:10,790
What's wrong?

323
00:21:11,350 --> 00:21:13,720
What do you mean by "what's wrong"?

324
00:21:14,110 --> 00:21:17,880
As your mother, I have to come see where you live.

325
00:21:18,370 --> 00:21:19,390
Mother?

326
00:21:21,520 --> 00:21:22,430
Are you friends?

327
00:21:23,830 --> 00:21:24,730
Um...

328
00:21:24,870 --> 00:21:25,230
I...

329
00:21:25,240 --> 00:21:27,300
Yes, we're friends.

330
00:21:28,770 --> 00:21:30,100
I see.

331
00:21:30,120 --> 00:21:32,490
Kosuke's always been in your care.

332
00:21:32,580 --> 00:21:34,310
No, I should be the one thanking you…

333
00:21:35,870 --> 00:21:36,640
If you were coming.

334
00:21:36,710 --> 00:21:38,050
You could at least let me know first.

335
00:21:38,430 --> 00:21:41,630
Because you never pick up the phone, Kosuke.

336
00:21:41,900 --> 00:21:43,570
I was really worried.

337
00:21:43,860 --> 00:21:45,380
Why didn't you answer the phone?

338
00:21:46,190 --> 00:21:47,190
I'm sorry.

339
00:21:47,320 --> 00:21:48,170
Forget it.

340
00:21:48,560 --> 00:21:51,000
I'll be living in Tokyo from now on, too.

341
00:21:51,740 --> 00:21:52,500
Huh?

342
00:21:53,170 --> 00:21:57,030
Didn't we talk about this before?
Let's live together in Tokyo.

343
00:21:57,240 --> 00:21:58,610
Did you forget?

344
00:21:59,360 --> 00:22:01,030
No... but...

345
00:22:01,800 --> 00:22:03,700
I don't have any plans to move for now.

346
00:22:04,290 --> 00:22:05,840
And besides, if we're going to live together in my current room…

347
00:22:05,840 --> 00:22:07,760
I don't mind living in a smaller place.

348
00:22:08,150 --> 00:22:09,950
Because we're a family.

349
00:22:12,130 --> 00:22:13,630
Oh, right.

350
00:22:14,160 --> 00:22:15,880
How about the three of us go out and have some fun later?

351
00:22:16,500 --> 00:22:17,350
Huh?

352
00:22:17,490 --> 00:22:19,580
I would like to check out a shop.

353
00:22:19,990 --> 00:22:20,790
Is that okay?

354
00:22:21,250 --> 00:22:22,560
No, but…

355
00:22:22,610 --> 00:22:25,800
Because it just feels bad to send a friend home.

356
00:22:26,540 --> 00:22:28,020
What's your name?

357
00:22:28,970 --> 00:22:30,620
My name is Kanade Shinichiro.

358
00:22:31,020 --> 00:22:33,250
Oh, so your name is Shinichiro.

359
00:22:33,540 --> 00:22:35,530
You're really good-looking.

360
00:22:36,090 --> 00:22:37,790
If the three of us walk together.

361
00:22:37,870 --> 00:22:41,910
Being sandwiched between two handsome guys
would look like I own a harem.

362
00:22:43,110 --> 00:22:44,310
Right? Kosuke…

363
00:22:48,030 --> 00:22:49,370
Don't touch Kanade.

364
00:22:49,900 --> 00:22:50,610
Huh?

365
00:22:51,950 --> 00:22:52,760
Mashiro?

366
00:22:56,120 --> 00:22:56,950
Don't…

367
00:22:58,460 --> 00:22:59,460
Don't get in my way.

368
00:23:08,900 --> 00:23:10,080
What do you mean by that?

369
00:23:26,910 --> 00:23:28,140
Please…

370
00:23:31,770 --> 00:23:33,270
Stop getting in my way…

371
00:24:45,690 --> 00:24:46,860
(Next Episode)
You've really been through a lot, haven't you.

372
00:24:46,860 --> 00:24:48,430
(Deepening conflict with mother)
I thought I was fine.

373
00:24:48,630 --> 00:24:49,740
Kanade is the most important person to me.

374
00:24:49,740 --> 00:24:51,810
(When to reveal your true feelings...)
Didn't I tell you not to say that?

375
00:24:51,950 --> 00:24:52,760
Kanade is...

376
00:24:52,980 --> 00:24:54,720
I'm not going anywhere.

377
00:24:54,720 --> 00:24:56,300
Kanade, I'm really glad you're here.

378
00:24:56,520 --> 00:24:57,840
I really want to be with Mashiro...

379
00:24:57,910 --> 00:24:59,780
Is it really okay?
